  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And the servants of Absalom did unto Amnon as Absalom had commanded,.... They smote him, and killed him, when he gave the word: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "then all the king's sons arose; from the feast, imagining they were all designed to be slain: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and every man gat him up upon his mule, and fled; creatures much used in Judea instead of horses, which, though they might not be bred, might be used (o). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(o) Vid. Misn. Celaim, c. 8. sect. 1.",
